    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">At this point, we&apos;ve covered all of the syntax of Smalltalk. Everything else is part of the class library. Have you noticed anything missing? How about </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">if-then-else</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> or </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">while</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> loops? Smalltalk just uses blocks and ordinary message sends. </text></para>
